use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dob1665702981390.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dob1665702981390.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dob1665702981390.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dob1665702981390\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n       Determining the Keyboard\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"dob1665702981390__determining_the_keyboard_189345\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface use the several mechanisms to determine which keyboard translation table to use for input.\n </p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dob1665702981390__li_d27617e1_d27618e1_d27619e1\">Operating system defaults—for example, on Unix the\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">TERM</code> environment variable indicates what kind of terminal is being\n            used. <p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63398e1_d63399e1_d63400e1\">If no other assignments are present, Uniface\n               uses the default obtained from the operating system to determine the keyboard\n               translation table used.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dob1665702981390__li_d27620e1_d27621e1_d27622e1\">Operating system symbols—if UKEYB is defined, it overrides the system default for the keybaord.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63401e1_d63402e1_d63403e1\">If the devices used are applicable for everyone at your site, it is advisable to use operating system symbols to define the keyboard value. The definition should be placed in a system-wide logon script, if there is one.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dob1665702981390__li_d27623e1_d27624e1_d27625e1\">Assignment files—if the keyboard translation table you want to use is not in the default library (USYS), the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$KEYBOARD</code> and <code class=\"ph codeph\">$VARIATION</code> settings must be defined in the assignment file. It is good practice to set the library explicitly, however, to prevent someone else from inadvertently setting it to a library that does not contain the specified keyboard.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63404e1_d63405e1_d63406e1\">If specific applications use different values, it is better to define them in a Uniface assignment file than rely on the other mechanisms.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dob1665702981390__li_d27626e1_d27627e1_d27628e1\">ProcScript statements—the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$keyboard</code> ProcScript function enables the user to switch between different keyboard layouts at different points in the application.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63407e1_d63408e1_d63409e1\">If the change in tables is a transitory one, for example, from numeric to keypad, and back again, the change should be handled within the application using ProcScript.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dob1665702981390__topic_d41787e1_d41788e1_d41789e1_d41790e1_d41791e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1172231e92\">\n                       \n Setting UKEYB\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63413e1_d63414e1_d63415e1\">The UKEYB symbol overrides the system keyboard default. It has different names under each operating system and is set in different ways. For example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dob1665702981390__li_d27629e1_d27630e1_d27631e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63416e1_d63417e1_d63418e1\">Under Windows, set the UKEYB environment variable.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dob1665702981390__li_d27632e1_d27633e1_d27634e1\">Under the Unix shell <code class=\"ph codeph\">(sh)</code>, use the following command to set the environment variable:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">UKEYB=vtnum;export UKEYB\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63419e1_d63420e1_d63421e1\">Uppercase variables have priority over lowercase ones.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dob1665702981390__p_d63422e1_d63423e1_d63424e1\">Refer to the operating system documentation for details.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526903\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Determining the Keyboard Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Determining the Keyboard Uniface use the several mechanisms to determine which keyboard translation table to use for input. Operating system defaults—for example, on Unix the TERM environment variable indicates what kind of terminal is being used. If no other assignments are present, Uniface uses the default obtained from the operating system to determine the keyboard translation table used. Operating system symbols—if UKEYB is defined, it overrides the system default for the keybaord. If the devices used are applicable for everyone at your site, it is advisable to use operating system symbols to define the keyboard value. The definition should be placed in a system-wide logon script, if there is one. Assignment files—if the keyboard translation table you want to use is not in the default library (USYS), the $KEYBOARD and $VARIATION settings must be defined in the assignment file. It is good practice to set the library explicitly, however, to prevent someone else from inadvertently setting it to a library that does not contain the specified keyboard. If specific applications use different values, it is better to define them in a Uniface assignment file than rely on the other mechanisms. ProcScript statements—the $keyboard ProcScript function enables the user to switch between different keyboard layouts at different points in the application. If the change in tables is a transitory one, for example, from numeric to keypad, and back again, the change should be handled within the application using ProcScript. Setting UKEYB The UKEYB symbol overrides the system keyboard default. It has different names under each operating system and is set in different ways. For example: Under Windows, set the UKEYB environment variable. Under the Unix shell (sh) , use the following command to set the environment variable: UKEYB=vtnum;export UKEYB Copy Uppercase variables have priority over lowercase ones. Refer to the operating system documentation for details. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}